kernel_variant.question:
Let $n\ge 1$ be an integer and let $q\in\mathbb C\setminus\{0\}$ be a (complex) parameter.  
For a permutation $\pi\in S_{n}$ denote by  
\[
\sigma(\pi)=
\begin{cases}
+1,&\text{if $\pi$ is even},\\[2pt]
-1,&\text{if $\pi$ is odd},
\end{cases}
\qquad 
\nu(\pi)=\#\{\text{fixed points of }\pi\}.
\]

A)  Show that  
\[
\boxed{\;
\sum_{\pi\in S_{n}}
\frac{\sigma(\pi)\,q^{\,n-\nu(\pi)}}{\nu(\pi)+1}
\;=\;
\frac{(1-q)^{n}\bigl(qn+1\bigr)-(-q)^{n}\,q n}{n+1}}
\tag{A}
\]

B)  Establish the exponential generating function  
\[
\boxed{\;
\sum_{n=0}^{\infty}
\left(
\sum_{\pi\in S_{n}}
\frac{\sigma(\pi)\,q^{\,n-\nu(\pi)}}{\nu(\pi)+1}
\right)\frac{t^{n}}{n!}
=
\frac{(1+q t)\bigl(e^{(1-q)t}-e^{-q t}\bigr)}{t}}
\tag{B}
\]

(N.B.\ The summand with $n=0$ is required only in the generating function; both formulas remain valid for $n=0$.)

Setting $q=2$ recovers the kernel variant, while $q=1$ yields the original exercise.

